2. Loop over all rows from 2 to ws.max_row.
3. For each row, read the three number cells (B, C, D). If any are None, treat them as 0 (the existing data uses zeros for missing values). Convert to integers, sort, and format as a three‑character string with leading zeros (`"{:03d}"` for each number, then concatenate).
4. Write the string to column G (cell G{row}).
5. Apply a bold Font and a PatternFill with the required hex color.
